DAEMONSET (Using Your Framework)
🔹 What is it?

DaemonSet ensures a pod runs on every node in the cluster.

🔹 Why we use it?

Because some services need to run on all nodes for monitoring or logging.

🔹 Where it is used?

Logging agents (Fluentd), monitoring agents, security tools.

🔹 How it works?

Kubernetes automatically deploys one pod per node and adds it when new nodes join.

🎤 Interview Answer

“For logging or monitoring, we need an agent on every node. So we use DaemonSet to ensure one pod runs on each node automatically.”
